text.tspan: Population density vs. GDP per capita, 2022
Population density is the number of people per km² of land area. GDP per capita is adjusted for inflation and
differences in the cost of living between countries.
Data source: HYDE (2023); Gapminder (2022); UN WPP (2024); UN FAO (2024); World Bank (2023); UN WPP (2024)
Note: GDP per capita is expressed in international-$ at 2017 prices.
